00:06:03,820 --> 00:06:05,820
JA: I don't know. I guess people can see

144
00:06:05,820 --> 00:06:08,820
the gross disparity in force.

145
00:06:08,820 --> 00:06:10,820
You have guys walking in a relaxed way down the street,

146
00:06:10,820 --> 00:06:13,820
and then an Apache helicopter sitting up at one kilometer

147
00:06:13,820 --> 00:06:15,820
firing 30-millimeter cannon shells

148
00:06:15,820 --> 00:06:17,820
on everyone --

149
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:20,820
looking for any excuse to do so --

150
00:06:20,820 --> 00:06:22,820
and killing people rescuing the wounded.

151
00:06:22,820 --> 00:06:25,820
And there was two journalists involved that clearly weren't insurgents

152
00:06:25,820 --> 00:06:27,820
because that's their full-time job.

153
00:06:29,820 --> 00:06:32,820
CA: I mean, there's been this U.S. intelligence analyst,

154
00:06:32,820 --> 00:06:34,820
Bradley Manning, arrested,

155
00:06:34,820 --> 00:06:37,820
and it's alleged that he confessed in a chat room

156
00:06:37,820 --> 00:06:40,820
to have leaked this video to you,

157
00:06:40,820 --> 00:06:42,820
along with 280,000

158
00:06:42,820 --> 00:06:44,820
classified U.S. embassy cables.

159
00:06:44,820 --> 00:06:47,820
I mean, did he?

160
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:49,820
JA: We have denied receiving those cables.

161
00:06:49,820 --> 00:06:51,820
He has been charged,

162
00:06:51,820 --> 00:06:53,820
about five days ago,

163
00:06:53,820 --> 00:06:56,820
with obtaining 150,000 cables

164
